assume (( 0 ) < r & r < 1);
then A7: ( ( r * M ) + ( ( 1 - r ) * M ) ) c= M by A6;
assume (u in M & v in M);
then (( r * u ) in ( r * M ) & ( ( 1 - r ) * v ) in { ( ( 1 - r ) * w ) where w is (Element of V): w in M });
then ( ( r * u ) + ( ( 1 - r ) * v ) ) in { ( p + q ) where p is (Element of V),q is (Element of V): (p in ( r * M ) & q in ( ( 1 - r ) * M )) };
then ( ( r * u ) + ( ( 1 - r ) * v ) ) in ( ( r * M ) + ( ( 1 - r ) * M ) ) by RUSUB_4:def 9;
hence thesis by A7;
end;
hence thesis by A1;
